NAF.raw: https : / / law . marquette . edu / national - sports - law - institute / volume - 7 - 1 Jim O'Brien was terminated from his position as head men's basketball coach at Ohio State University following the disclosure that he loaned a recruit's mother money . O'Brien sued , claiming he was terminated without cause , and both parties filed motions for summary judgment . The court of claims denied the motions because there was a factual dispute concerning what constituted a material breach under the employment contract .
